# 🎛️ Acoustic Design Engine: Prompt Engineering Templates

These templates are designed for the **Acoustic Design Module** of AethelFrame. They steer the neural audio synthesis model by defining simulated "anatomy," material resonance, and spatial processing to create convincing voices for non-human or mythic subjects.

---

## 📜 1. Universal Master Template
Use this structure to construct custom voice profiles. Replace bracketed variables `[...]` with specific traits.

```text
[ROLE]: Define subject (e.g., "Ancient Dragon", "Sentient Sword", "Human Explorer").

🧬 VOCAL ANATOMY SIMULATION:
- Vocal Tract: [Length/Shape] (e.g., "Elongated tube", "Short/Squeaky", "Wide/Cavernous")
- Resonance Chambers: [Body Part] (e.g., "Chest cavity", "Carapace", "Hollow glass center")
- Articulator Type: [Mechanism] (e.g., "Lips/Tongue (Human)", "Guttural/Throat", "Vibration/Synthesis", "Telepathic")

🔊 MATERIAL & TEXTURE:
- Timbre Base: [Quality] (e.g., "Warm baritone", "Gravelly stone", "Sharp metallic", "Breathy mist")
- Surface Interaction: [Effect] (e.g., "Fur muffling", "Scale clicking undertones", "Crystal ringing overtones")
- Distortion Level: [0.0 to 1.0] (e.g., "0.1 for slight grit", "0.8 for demonic corruption")

🌌 SPATIAL & HARMONIC FX:
- Harmonic Layers: [Count] (e.g., "Single voice", "Choral triad", "Sub-bass rumble")
- Reverb Environment: [Space] (e.g., "Dry close-up", "Cathedral hall", "Void/No air")
- Pitch Modulation: [Type] (e.g., "Steady", "Undulating/Liquid", "Glitchy/Unstable")

🎭 PERFORMANCE DIRECTION:
- Emotional State: [Mood] (e.g., "Weary", "Manically energetic", "Coldly logical")
- Pacing Style: [Rhythm] (e.g., "Slow/Deliberate", "Rapid/Jittery", "Ethereal/Timeless")
```

