## 🛑 4. Anti-Hallucination & Safety Directives
AI audio models often introduce artifacts when pushed too far. Include these instructions in your system prompt to ensure clean output.

**⚠️ Negative Prompts (What to Avoid):**
> "Do not generate popping sounds (plosives). No metallic clipping. Avoid 'robotic warbling' outside of specific directives. Do not hallucinate background music. Maintain consistent timbre throughout the duration. No slurping or wet mouth noises."

**🔧 Stability Constraints:**
> - **Duration Limit:** If `harmonic_layers > 3`, enforce a `tempo_multiplier` of at least `0.9` to prevent synthesis collision artifacts.
> - **Articulation Check:** If `articulation_type` is `Telepathic` or `Non-Vocal`, ensure the phoneme recognizer forces a minimum consonant sharpness of `0.6` to maintain transcript readability.

